  "prompt": "Does the law differentiate between intentional and unintentional money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, the law generally distinguishes between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering involves deliberate actions to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds, while unintentional money laundering can occur through negligence or lack of awareness. The penalties and legal consequences differ based on the level of intent.\n\nIntentional money laundering typically involves:\n- Deliberate attempts to hide illegal funds\n- Knowingly participating in financial transactions to disguise criminal proceeds\n- More severe criminal penalties\n- Potential federal prosecution\n\nUnintentional money laundering might involve:\n- Accidental involvement without knowledge of illegal activities\n- Lack of proper due diligence\n- Potentially lower penalties\n- Opportunity to demonstrate lack of intent\n\nHowever, the specific details can vary by jurisdiction and specific circumstances of each case.",
